---
import { Icon } from 'astro-icon/components';
import SectionTitle from '@/components/common/SectionTitle.astro';
import Button from '@/components/ui/Button.astro';
---

<section id="faq" class="relative mx-auto mt-32 mb-32 max-w-6xl px-4">
  <div class="mb-12 text-center">
    <SectionTitle>FAQ</SectionTitle>
    <h2 class="mb-6 text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-white md:text-5xl">Frequently asked questions</h2>
  </div>

  <div class="space-y-6">
    <details class="group cursor-pointer rounded-lg border border-white/10 bg-white/5 transition hover:bg-white/10">
      <summary class="flex w-full items-center justify-between px-6 py-5 text-lg font-semibold text-white select-none">
        Which Windows versions are supported?
        <Icon name="tabler:chevron-down" class="h-5 w-5 flex-shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" />
      </summary>
      <div class="px-6 pb-6">
        <p class="leading-relaxed text-white/70">
          AtlasOS officially supports <span class="font-semibold text-white">Windows 11</span>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details class="group cursor-pointer rounded-lg border border-white/10 bg-white/5 transition hover:bg-white/10">
      <summary class="flex w-full items-center justify-between px-6 py-5 text-lg font-semibold text-white select-none">
        Will my apps keep working?
        <Icon name="tabler:chevron-down" class="h-5 w-5 flex-shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" />
      </summary>
      <div class="px-6 pb-6">
        <p class="leading-relaxed text-white/70">
          Yes! AtlasOS is the same as standard Windows, we support all functionality and all anti-cheats. There is
          nothing stripped from AtlasOS, giving you the same experience as standard Windows.
        </p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details class="group cursor-pointer rounded-lg border border-white/10 bg-white/5 transition hover:bg-white/10">
      <summary class="flex w-full items-center justify-between px-6 py-5 text-lg font-semibold text-white select-none">
        How do I install AtlasOS?
        <Icon name="tabler:chevron-down" class="h-5 w-5 flex-shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" />
      </summary>
      <div class="px-6 pb-6">
        <p class="leading-relaxed text-white/70">
          It is required that everyone choosing to install AtlasOS follows our
          <a
            href="https://docs.atlasos.net/getting-started/installation/"
            class="text-primary hover:text-primary"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">installation documentation</a
          >. If you do not follow our
          <a
            href="https://docs.atlasos.net/getting-started/installation/"
            class="text-primary hover:text-primary"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">installation documentation</a
          > your installation of AtlasOS will be unsupported.
        </p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details class="group cursor-pointer rounded-lg border border-white/10 bg-white/5 transition hover:bg-white/10">
      <summary class="flex w-full items-center justify-between px-6 py-5 text-lg font-semibold text-white select-none">
        Can I easily roll back to stock Windows?
        <Icon name="tabler:chevron-down" class="h-5 w-5 flex-shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" />
      </summary>
      <div class="px-6 pb-6">
        <p class="leading-relaxed text-white/70">
          No, AtlasOS does not provide a rollback or recovery option. You will need to reinstall Windows, just the same
          as you would need to reinstall Windows to install AtlasOS. We have a guide on how to do this in our
          <a
            href="https://docs.atlasos.net/getting-started/reverting-atlas/"
            class="text-primary hover:text-primary"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">reverting AtlasOS documentation</a
          >.
        </p>
      </div>
    </details>
  </div>
  <div class="mt-8 text-center">
    <Button
      href="https://docs.atlasos.net/general-faq/atlas-and-security/"
      icon="tabler:arrow-up-right"
      iconPosition="after"
      external
      variant="tertiary"
      size="lg"
    >
      View more FAQs in our documentation
    </Button>
  </div>
</section>
